AND THE FIBROIDS
COULD EVENTUALLY INTERFERE--

11:05.542 --> 11:08.917
ALL RIGHT. WE GET IT.
WE'VE GOTTA GO FOR IT NOW.

11:08.959 --> 11:11.041
LOOK, THEY SAID
YOU'RE OVULATING.

11:11.083 --> 11:14.750
DOESN'T THAT MEAN
WE'RE IN THE ZONE TO TRY?

11:14.792 --> 11:18.041
THAT'S--THAT'S RIGHT. YES.

11:18.083 --> 11:20.208
ARE YOU SURE
YOU'RE OKAY WITH THIS?

11:20.250 --> 11:22.000
CATHLEEN, I LOVE YOU.

11:22.041 --> 11:25.000
IT'S WHAT YOU WANT,
WHAT I WANT.

11:27.166 --> 11:29.041
I'M SURE.

11:30.834 --> 11:32.792
SO WHAT'S WRONG
WITH DELL'S GRANDDAD?

11:32.834 --> 11:35.417
OH, IT'S JUST SOME
MINOR BUMPS AND BRUISES.

11:35.458 --> 11:38.417
DELL'S CONCERNED THAT THERE
MIGHT BE SOME ABUSE GOING ON,

11:38.458 --> 11:41.542
BUT NATE AND WENDELL ARE ADAMANT
THAT THAT'S NOT HAPPENING.

11:41.583 --> 11:43.542
WELL, DELL'S GRANDFATHER
IS A WAR VET.

11:43.583 --> 11:47.792
I THINK HE'D BE TOO PROUD
TO ADMIT SOMETHING LIKE THAT.
WHERE'S THE MOM?

11:47.834 --> 11:49.792
DELL'S ALWAYS GETTING
THOSE POSTCARDS FROM INDIA

11:49.834 --> 11:51.792
AND CHINA
AND ALL OVER THE PLACE?
YEAH, I ASKED HIM ONCE.

11:51.834 --> 11:54.667
HE SAID THAT
SHE WAS A ROLLING STONE.
YEAH, SHE ROLLED RIGHT OFF

11:54.709 --> 11:56.667
AND LEFT DELL
WITH HIS GRANDPARENTS.

11:56.709 --> 11:58.750
WENDELL WENT INTO A HOME
AFTER HIS WIFE DIED.

11:58.792 --> 12:01.041
WOW. YOU SURE KNOW
A LOT ABOUT DELL.
SERIOUSLY,

12:01.083 --> 12:03.041
IF DELL SUSPECTS SOMETHING,
THEN MAYBE YOU SHOULD--

12:03.083 --> 12:06.041
I JUST READ A PAPER
ABOUT ELDER ABUSE.

12:06.083 --> 12:09.041
IT'S WAY UNDERREPORTED.
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL CALL THE NURSING HOME,

12:09.083 --> 12:11.375
SEE IF I CAN GET AHOLD
OF HIS MEDICAL RECORDS.

12:11.417 --> 12:13.041
HEY, SAM.

12:13.083 --> 12:15.917
TELL ME WHAT THAT
WAS ABOUT EARLIER.

12:15.959 --> 12:18.041
OH. UH...

12:18.083 --> 12:20.792
I JUST THINK
THAT IT WOULD BE NICE

12:20.834 --> 12:22.875
IF WE KEPT
THIS THING PRIVATE.

12:22.917 --> 12:24.875
WELL, SOMEBODY ALREADY
FOUND OUT, SAM.

12:24.917 --> 12:27.166
AND HONESTLY, I DON'T THINK
IT'S THAT BIG OF A DEAL.

12:27.208 --> 12:30.041
OH.
WHAT, ARE--ARE YOU AFRAID THAT
THIS IS GONNA MEAN COMMITMENT?

12:30.083 --> 12:31.166
WHAT? BECAUSE IF, YOU KNOW,

12:31.208 --> 12:33.667
YOU'RE ASHAMED OF HAVING SEX
WITH YOUR EX-WIFE--
NAOMI--

12:33.709 --> 12:35.709
UM, NAOMI, I GOT THESE LABS
FOR YOUR PATIENT--

12:35.750 --> 12:38.125
JUST LEAVE IT ON MY DESK.
EXCUSE ME.
(sputters)

12:38.166 --> 12:39.625
ALL RIGHT. SORRY.

12:39.667 --> 12:40.875
YEAH.

12:40.917 --> 12:42.041
JEEZ.

12:42.083 --> 12:44.041
THEY'RE REALLY
GOING AT IT LATELY.

12:44.083 --> 12:47.041
ONE MINUTE, THEY'RE GRINNING,
THEN THE NEXT MINUTE THEY'RE--

12:47.083 --> 12:49.083
YOU THINK THEY'RE
"GOING AT IT"?

12:49.125 --> 12:50.875
SEX?
YEAH.

12:50.917 --> 12:54.041
NO. NO.
YOU THINK SO?

12:54.083 --> 12:56.041
AS MUCH AS THEY ARGUE?

12:56.083 --> 12:59.291
ANGRY SEX IS HOT.

12:59.333 --> 13:01.083
(scoffs)

13:03.542 --> 13:05.500
SO I CALLED THE NURSING HOME,

13:05.542 --> 13:08.208
AND THEY SENT OVER WENDELL
AND NATE'S MEDICAL RECORDS.

13:08.250 --> 13:10.500
THERE ARE A BUNCH
OF INJURY REPORTS

13:10.542 --> 13:13.333
IN THE PAST FEW MONTHS--
MINOR SCRAPES, BRUISES.

13:13.375 --> 13:15.583
SO I WAS RIGHT
TO BE CONCERNED.

13:15.625 --> 13:18.166
WELL, IT'S NOT PROOF
OF ANYTHING, BUT, YEAH,

13:18.208 --> 13:20.166
YOU WERE RIGHT
TO BE CONCERNED.

13:20.208 --> 13:24.041
I'M GONNA GO OVER THERE
AND CHECK THIS OUT.
I'LL GO WITH YOU.

13:24.083 --> 13:26.333
NO, I CAN HANDLE THIS, OKAY?
NO, YOU BROUGHT THEM TO ME,

13:26.375 --> 13:27.792
SO TECHNICALLY,
THEY'RE MY PATIENTS,

13:27.834 --> 13:29.709
WHICH MEANS LEGALLY,
I'M AS OBLIGATED TO THEM

13:29.750 --> 13:32.041
AS ANYONE ELSE.
I TOLD YOU, I-I DON'T--

13:32.083 --> 13:33.375
DELL, I'M GOING.

13:36.542 --> 13:41.291
(Cooper) ALL RIGHT, LET'S START
BY PICKING UP OUR BABIES.

13:41.333 --> 13:44.333
BUT WITH TWO HANDS.

13:44.375 --> 13:47.834
MY BABY LOOKS LIKE CHUCKY.
DO YOU WANT TO TRADE?

13:47.875 --> 13:49.750
NO WAY.
ALL RIGHT,
NO TRADING BABIES.

13:49.792 --> 13:53.041
ONE OF THE THINGS WE'RE TRYING
TO TEACH YOU IN THIS CLASS

13:53.083 --> 13:56.041
IS HOW TO BOND
WITH YOUR NEWBORN.
I DON'T WANT TO BOND
WITH CHUCKY.

13:56.083 --> 13:58.041
THESE BABIES ARE GONNA
COME INTO YOUR LIFE,

13:58.083 --> 14:00.041
AND THEY'RE GONNA SEEM
SO SMALL AND FRAGILE

14:00.083 --> 14:02.125
THAT YOU'RE GONNA BE AFRAID
TO TOUCH THEM.

14:02.166 --> 14:04.333
DON'T BE.
UH, THEY NEED TO BE HELD,

14:04.375 --> 14:07.333
AND THEY'RE A LOT TOUGHER
THAN THEY LOOK.

14:07.375 --> 14:09.125
YEAH, I HEARD A BABY CAN EAT,

14:09.166 --> 14:12.041
LIKE, HALF A CUP OF SAND
AND BE FINE.
THAT'S NOT--

14:12.083 --> 14:14.166
AND WHAT ABOUT THAT BABY
THAT FELL 11 STORIES,

14:14.208 --> 14:17.041
CRAWLED AWAY
WITHOUT A SCRATCH?

14:17.083 --> 14:20.041
IT'S WHAT YOU SAID, MAN.
YOU CAN'T BREAK A BABY.
(Cooper) YEAH, YOU--YOU CAN.

14:20.083 --> 14:21.417
FROM 11 STORIES,
TOTALLY BREAKABLE.

14:21.458 --> 14:23.458
UM, WHO--
WHO'S YOUR PEDIATRICIAN?

14:23.500 --> 14:26.458
YOU KNOW WHAT? WHY DON'T WE
START WITH THE BASICS?

14:26.500 --> 14:29.667
YES. UM...
CHANGING A DIAPER.

14:29.709 --> 14:32.083
WHO WANTS TO GIVE IT
A TRY?

14:36.208 --> 14:38.417
I'D LIKE TO TRY.

14:38.458 --> 14:40.000
ADAM--OUR FIRST VOLUNTEER.

14:40.041 --> 14:42.041
LET'S DO THIS.
DR. PETE?

14:42.083 --> 14:44.041
OKAY, GENTLEMEN,
PUT YOUR BABIES DOWN.

14:44.083 --> 14:47.041
SUPPORT THE HEAD. SUPPORT--
NEXT TIME, SUPPORT THE HEAD.

14:47.083 --> 14:49.500
(Dell) HE'S PROBABLY
WITH NATE OR ARTHUR.

14:49.542 --> 14:52.041
THEY PLAY BINGO TOGETHER.
WHERE IS EVERYBODY?

14:52.083 --> 14:54.500
HERE. (clears throat)

14:56.458 --> 14:58.291
WE'RE LOOKING FOR WENDELL.
HE'S IN ROOM 310.

14:58.333 --> 15:00.458
YEAH.
DO YOU KNOW WHERE HE IS?

15:00.500 --> 15:02.375
UH, IF HE'S NOT IN HIS ROOM,
I DON'T--

15:02.417 --> 15:05.375
NO, WE CHECKED HIS ROOM.
HE'S NOT THERE, OKAY?

15:05.417 --> 15:07.667
AREN'T YOU SUPPOSED TO BE
WATCHING THEM?

15:07.709 --> 15:10.625
(sighs) THEY GIVE ME
$5 AN HOUR NOT TO.

15:10.667 --> 15:14.041
IF YOU CAN DO BETTER...

15:15.625 --> 15:18.083
YOU THINK THAT GUY
WAS JUST MESSING WITH US?

15:18.125 --> 15:21.041
I SHOULD--I SHOULD'VE
GIVEN HIM A 20.

15:21.083 --> 15:22.750
(faint cheering)

15:22.792 --> 15:24.291
YOU HEAR THAT?

15:24.333 --> 15:27.417
YEAH, I HEAR IT.

15:27.458 --> 15:30.417
(cheering grows louder)

15:30.458 --> 15:33.333
(all yelling at once)

15:33.375 --> 15:36.333
(crowd cheering)

15:36.375 --> 15:38.750
OH!
(cheering continues)

15:40.083 --> 15:44.667
(cheering)

15:44.709 --> 15:49.667
(crowd yelling indistinctly)

15:49.709 --> 15:52.125
STOP, STOP! YOU TWO
ARE GONNA KILL EACH OTHER.

15:52.166 --> 15:53.959
WHOA!

15:54.000 --> 15:56.041
(crowd yelling)
PA PA!

15:56.083 --> 15:58.458
STAY OUTTA THIS.
THIS IS A CHAMPIONSHIP MATCH.

15:58.500 --> 16:01.291
AND I DON'T WANT HIM
MAKING EXCUSES

16:01.333 --> 16:03.083
WHEN I KICK HIS BUTT.
FIRST TIME FOR EVERYTHING.

16:03.125 --> 16:05.083
EXCEPT YOU
GROWING A PAIR.

16:05.125 --> 16:06.500
OH!

16:06.542 --> 16:09.375
(crowd yelling)

16:09.417 --> 16:12.041
COME ON. GET UP.
IS THAT ALL YOU GOT?

16:12.083 --> 16:14.041
OH, NO.
HIS HEART RATE'S DOWN TO 30.

16:14.083 --> 16:16.041
I CAN BARELY FEEL HIS PULSE.
HE'S HURT.

16:16.083 --> 16:18.333
SURE HE IS. COME ON.
GET UP, YOU OLD GEEZER.

16:18.375 --> 16:21.792
GET SOME MORE OF THIS.
NO, NO, GAME OVER.
HE'S REALLY HURT.

16:21.834 --> 16:23.125
WE GOTTA GET HIM
AN AMBULANCE.

16:23.166 --> 16:26.375
I NEED TO GET HIM
TO A HOSPITAL NOW.

16:26.417 --> 16:28.041
(Cooper) GOOD FIRST DAY,
YOU GUYS.

16:28.083 --> 16:30.834
CHECK YOUR BABIES
AT THE DOOR.

16:30.875 --> 16:33.041
GUYS, UH, THAT WAS AMAZING.

16:33.083 --> 16:36.125
UM, I WAS JUST WONDERING
IF THERE'S ANY HOMEWORK.
NO, NO HOMEWORK.

16:36.166 --> 16:38.583
YOU KNOW, ADAM, YOUR ENERGY
IS GREAT FOR THIS CLASS,

16:38.625 --> 16:40.583
AND IT'S OKAY TO BE NERVOUS.

16:40.625 --> 16:43.583
THAT'S TOTALLY NORMAL
FOR A FIRST-TIME DAD.
OH, THANKS,
BUT I'M ACTUALLY NOT A DAD.

16:43.625 --> 16:46.375
I'M JUST HERE FOR JACK.
JACK IS YOUR PARTNER?

16:46.417 --> 16:49.083
OH, NO, NO. WELL, HE'S A PARTNER
AT THE FIRM, OF COURSE,

16:49.125 --> 16:51.917
BUT I'M JUST HIS ASSISTANT.

16:51.959 --> 16:54.125
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE
TAKING THE CLASS.
JACK IS YOUR BOSS?

16:54.166 --> 16:56.166
YEAH.
HE SENT--
HE SENT HIS ASSISTANT.

16:56.208 --> 16:58.041
WELL, SECOND ASSISTANT,
ACTUALLY, BUT, UH, NOT FOR LONG,

16:58.083 --> 17:02.083
THANKS TO THIS CLASS.
YOU NEED TO TELL HIM
TO BE HERE.

17:02.125 --> 17:04.041
OH, NO. NO, NO,
I COULDN'T TELL HIM THAT.

17:04.083 --> 17:06.208
HE'LL DESTROY ME
OR HAVE ME DESTROYED.

17:06.250 --> 17:08.750
LOOK, PLEASE J--
ADAM, THE ONLY REQUIREMENT
FOR THIS DAD'S CLASS

17:08.792 --> 17:10.750
IS YOU'RE ACTUALLY
GONNA BE A DAD,

17:10.792 --> 17:13.375
SO IF YOUR BOSS
WANTS TO TAKE THE CLASS,

17:13.417 --> 17:15.041
HE HAS TO ATTEND HIMSELF.

17:22.291 --> 17:24.041
HEY, YOU'RE STILL HERE?

17:24.083 --> 17:25.250
(sighs) CATHLEEN WENT BACK

17:25.291 --> 17:28.041
FOR ONE MORE LOOK
AT THE SPERM DONOR BOOK.

17:28.083 --> 17:30.542
SHE'S HOPING SOMETHING
WILL CLICK.

17:30.583 --> 17:33.125
I'M GONNA GIVE HER
THIS BABY.

17:33.166 --> 17:35.041
I BELIEVE YOU.

17:35.083 --> 17:36.625
YOU'RE DETERMINED.

17:36.667 --> 17:38.166
BUT...

17:38.208 --> 17:42.041
WHY SO DETERMINED?

17:42.083 --> 17:45.250
CATHLEEN NEVER ASKS
FOR MUCH.

17:45.291 --> 17:48.041
I PROMISED HER A HAPPY LIFE.

17:48.083 --> 17:50.291
SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO
GET OVER YOURSELF

17:50.333 --> 17:52.041
IN ORDER TO DO THAT.

17:52.083 --> 17:54.625
WELL, I WONDER HOW CATHLEEN
WOULD FEEL ABOUT THAT--

17:54.667 --> 17:56.709
YOU DISREGARDING
YOUR OWN FEELINGS

17:56.750 --> 17:58.834
TO GIVE HER
WHAT SHE WANTS.

17:58.875 --> 18:00.917
SHE DOESN'T
TALK ABOUT IT MUCH,

18:00.959 --> 18:02.917
BUT CATHLEEN WAS ADOPTED.

18:02.959 --> 18:05.041
I MEAN, SHE'S GOT
GREAT PARENTS, BUT...

18:05.083 --> 18:07.041
I WANTED TO GIVE HER
WHAT I HAD,

18:07.083 --> 18:08.375
YOU KNOW, MY FAMILY.

18:08.417 --> 18:10.041
THEY'RE CRAZY, BUT...

18:10.083 --> 18:12.500
IT'S ONLY FAIR
THAT SHE GETS TO HAVE

18:12.542 --> 18:15.041
ONE PERSON IN HER LIFE
THAT LOOKS LIKE HER.

18:15.083 --> 18:18.125
BUT WHAT ABOUT
WHAT YOU WANT, GEOFFREY?

18:18.166 --> 18:21.041
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
WHY DON'T YOU...

18:21.083 --> 18:24.041
GO HOME, GET SOME SLEEP,
THINK ABOUT IT,

18:24.083 --> 18:27.250
AND THEN START OVER
TOMORROW?

18:35.333 --> 18:37.250
H-HOW IS HE?

18:37.291 --> 18:40.041
WELL, HE, UH, HE HAD
A HEART ATTACK.

18:40.083 --> 18:42.750
WE'RE TRYING TO REOPEN
HIS BLOCKED VESSELS.

18:42.792 --> 18:46.041
I DID THAT?
I-I DID THAT TO HIM?

18:46.083 --> 18:49.041
WELL, I'M SURE IT DIDN'T HELP
THAT YOU DECKED HIM,

18:49.083 --> 18:52.875
BUT, UH, WE CAN'T SAY
RIGHT NOW.

18:52.917 --> 18:54.583
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

18:54.625 --> 18:57.041
WE--WE DIDN'T MEAN
FOR ANYONE TO GET HURT.

18:57.083 --> 18:59.041
OKAY, THEN WHY
DID YOU HIT EACH OTHER?

18:59.083 --> 19:01.208
WE HAD TO DO SOMETHING.

19:01.250 --> 19:02.917
THE DAYS THERE...

19:02.959 --> 19:04.917
YOU--YOU CAN'T
TELL ONE FROM ANOTHER.

19:04.959 --> 19:08.667
ME, NATE--
WE WERE ALL GOING CRAZY.

19:08.709 --> 19:11.041
YEAH, WELL,
THAT PART'S OBVIOUS.

19:11.083 --> 19:14.667
DELL, MAYBE YOUR GRANDDAD,
HE--HE JUST NEEDS A MINUTE--
I GOT IT.

19:14.709 --> 19:17.625
I NEED YOU TO SWEAR, OKAY?
NO MORE OF THIS.

19:17.667 --> 19:20.750
YOU THINK I DON'T KNOW
IT'S OVER?

19:26.458 --> 19:27.959
DELL...

19:32.250 --> 19:34.458
(sighs)

19:41.208 --> 19:43.041
OLD MAN FIGHT CLUB?

19:43.083 --> 19:44.583
OH, YEAH.

19:44.625 --> 19:47.041
WENDELL WAS
THE RINGLEADER, TOO.

19:47.083 --> 19:49.083
KNOCKED THE HELL
OUT OF HIS FRIEND,

19:49.125 --> 19:51.166
WHO'S ACTUALLY NOT DOING
TOO WELL NOW.

19:51.208 --> 19:53.041
WELL, IT'S AMAZING

19:53.083 --> 19:56.041
WHAT SOME PEOPLE WILL DO
TO ENTERTAIN THEMSELVES.
YEAH. COME HERE.

19:56.083 --> 19:57.542
WHAT? OH.

19:57.583 --> 20:00.166
OOH. OOH.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:00.208 --> 20:03.041
HMM? I'M JUST
ENTERTAINING MYSELF.

20:03.083 --> 20:05.041
AND YOU.
TRYING AT LEAST.
NO.

20:05.083 --> 20:07.417
COME HERE.
NO.

20:07.458 --> 20:09.333
SHH, SHH, SHH.
SAM, NO, NO.

20:09.375 --> 20:10.250
WHAT?

20:10.291 --> 20:12.000
NO.

20:14.291 --> 20:17.041
I'M NOT GONNA BE YOUR...
SECRET LOVER.

20:17.083 --> 20:19.875
OH, COME ON, NAOMI.

20:19.917 --> 20:24.000
YOU'RE MAD BECAUSE I'M TRYING
TO SPICE THINGS UP

20:24.041 --> 20:27.250
NOW THAT WE'RE...
WHATEVER WE ARE?

20:27.291 --> 20:29.250
OKAY, EVERYBODY AROUND HERE,

20:29.291 --> 20:31.208
THEY ALREADY WENT THROUGH
OUR DIVORCE.

20:31.250 --> 20:34.291
DO WE REALLY HAVE TO DRAG THEM
THROUGH EVERY LITTLE DETAIL NOW?

20:34.333 --> 20:36.083
THIS IS NOT ABOUT THEM.

20:36.125 --> 20:38.083
THIS IS ABOUT THINGS
BEING DIFFERENT

20:38.125 --> 20:41.041
THE SECOND TIME AROUND...

20:41.083 --> 20:45.041
IF THERE IS
A SECOND TIME AROUND.

20:45.083 --> 20:49.375
I NEED TO KNOW YOU'RE NOT
JUST GONNA GIVE UP THIS TIME.

20:49.417 --> 20:51.375
OH.
FORGET IT. I--

20:51.417 --> 20:54.041
I GOTTA GO. I-I HAVE TO GET--
WAIT, LISTEN.

20:54.083 --> 20:57.041
I HAVE A PATIENT.
NAOMI, WAIT.

20:57.083 --> 20:58.834
NAOMI, UH...

20:58.875 --> 21:01.458
YOUR PATIENT'S HERE.
YEAH, I KNOW.

21:01.500 --> 21:03.125
YEAH. YEAH.

21:03.166 --> 21:06.792
OH, UH, DELL, LISTEN,
I WAS LOOKING OVER

21:06.834 --> 21:09.417
SOME OF THESE MEDICAL REPORTS
FROM THE NURSING HOME--

21:09.458 --> 21:11.333
WHAT DID YOU DO TO HER?

21:11.375 --> 21:13.083
EXCUSE ME?

21:13.125 --> 21:14.959
YOU HEARD ME.
WHAT DID YOU DO?

21:15.000 --> 21:17.041
I DON'T THINK THAT'S
ANY OF YOUR BUSINESS.

21:17.083 --> 21:19.458
NO. IT IS, OKAY?
NO, IT'S NOT.

21:19.500 --> 21:21.417
DELL, I KNOW THAT YOU'RE
UPSET ABOUT WENDELL--

21:21.458 --> 21:23.959
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH HIM, OKAY?

21:24.000 --> 21:26.291
EVERY TIME SHE WALKS AWAY
FROM YOU, SHE'S MISERABLE.

21:26.333 --> 21:29.041
AND I CARE ABOUT HOW
SHE FEELS, OKAY? I CARE.
DELL--

21:29.083 --> 21:31.041
NO, I KNOW WHAT YOU THINK,

21:31.083 --> 21:33.041
BUT THIS ISN'T
JUST A CRUSH, OKAY?

21:33.083 --> 21:35.375
MAYBE AFTER SO MANY YEARS,
YOU JUST DON'T SEE IT.

21:35.417 --> 21:38.041
YOU KNOW HOW MANY WOMEN THINK
LIKE AND--AND LOOK LIKE THAT

21:38.083 --> 21:40.166
AND LAUGH LIKE THAT
AND CARE?

21:40.208 --> 21:42.166
ONE.
SO FAR I'VE MET ONE.

21:42.208 --> 21:44.667
AND YEAH, SHE'S--SHE'S OUT OF
MY LEAGUE IN EVERY POSSIBLE WAY,

21:44.709 --> 21:46.333
BUT I DON'T CARE.
SHE DAZZLES ME.

21:46.375 --> 21:49.375
AND I'M NOT STUPID ENOUGH
TO HOPE THAT ONE DAY I'LL MEET

21:49.417 --> 21:51.875
SOMEONE LIKE HER WHEN THE TIME
IS RIGHT, BECAUSE I WON'T.

21:51.917 --> 21:53.542
I LOVE HER. OKAY?

21:53.583 --> 21:56.792
AND I GUARANTEE YOU
I WOULDN'T MAKE HER CRY.

21:56.834 --> 21:59.291
OKAY, UH... DELL,
I KNOW THAT

21:59.333 --> 22:01.750
YOU'RE UNDER
A LOT OF STRESS RIGHT NOW,

22:01.792 --> 22:04.333
SO I'M GONNA PRETEND

22:04.375 --> 22:08.792
YOU DIDN'T JUST SAY
THOSE THINGS ABOUT MY WIFE.

22:08.834 --> 22:10.500
EX-WIFE.

22:18.000 --> 22:20.208
UH, I JUST WANTED
TO LET YOU KNOW,

22:20.250 --> 22:23.709
I'M GONNA DO MY JOB,
BUT I'M DONE WITH DELL.

22:23.750 --> 22:25.709
WHAT--HEY, WHAT HAPPENED?

22:25.750 --> 22:29.041
DELL IS A...
DELL'S A CHILD.

22:29.083 --> 22:31.333
SAM, WILL YOU CUT HIM
A BREAK?

22:31.375 --> 22:33.041
OH, YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

22:33.083 --> 22:35.792
I'M CUTTING HIM A BREAK...

22:35.834 --> 22:39.000
A BIG DAMN BREAK.

22:44.500 --> 22:48.041
WE PUT A LOCK
ON THE BASEMENT DOOR.

22:48.083 --> 22:50.041
THEY WERE TAKING BETS.
OKAY.

22:50.083 --> 22:52.041
THE WINNER WOULD WALK AROUND
ALL PUFFED UP.

22:52.083 --> 22:54.417
IT'S...
WHAT A THING, HUH?

22:54.458 --> 22:56.125
G-49.

22:56.166 --> 22:59.166
(people murmuring)

23:02.875 --> 23:05.417
HEY, PA PA.

23:08.083 --> 23:09.875
NATE?

23:09.917 --> 23:11.458
UH, THE SAME.

23:11.500 --> 23:14.041
THE DOCTORS PUT
A PACEMAKER IN.

23:14.083 --> 23:16.709
YOU SHOULDN'T
BLAME YOURSELF.

23:16.750 --> 23:18.709
HE DIDN'T
HAVE TO FIGHT YOU.

23:18.750 --> 23:22.500
I SHOULD'VE KNOWN BETTER.

23:27.458 --> 23:28.458
HEY.

23:28.500 --> 23:31.041
STILL NO CLICK.

23:31.083 --> 23:33.041
WHERE'S GEOFFREY?
ON HIS WAY.

23:33.083 --> 23:35.041
IT'S NOT LIKE WE HAVEN'T
GONE OVER THESE GUYS

23:35.083 --> 23:37.041
A MILLION TIMES.
HMM.

23:37.083 --> 23:39.417
HEY.
HEY, I THINK
I'VE SOLVED OUR PROBLEM.

23:39.458 --> 23:41.291
I HAVE FOUND
THE PERFECT DONOR.

23:41.333 --> 23:43.458
YOU--MARK.

23:43.500 --> 23:45.750
DR. MONTGOMERY, I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET MY BROTHER.

23:45.792 --> 23:48.041
YOUR BROTHER?

23:48.083 --> 23:50.542
HEY, YEAH.
LET'S MAKE A KID.

23:50.583 --> 23:52.625
(chuckles)

23:52.667 --> 23:55.041
(Charlotte) SO IT'S TRUE.

23:57.125 --> 23:59.750
I HAD TO SEE IT
FOR MYSELF.

23:59.792 --> 24:03.041
YOU STOLE MY DADS.
YOU TOOK MY CLASS ROSTER.

24:03.083 --> 24:05.041
I JUST HAD TO REFUND
$27,000.

24:05.083 --> 24:08.041
YOU KNOW HOW THAT LOOKS
FOR THE CHIEF OF STAFF?

24:08.083 --> 24:10.291
SEE HOW IT FEELS
TO BE SOMEONE'S BITCH?

24:10.333 --> 24:13.041
I SEE.
THIS IS A GAME TO YOU.

24:13.083 --> 24:15.917
OH, AND IT'S NOT FOR YOU?
COME ON.

24:15.959 --> 24:18.166
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WE'RE OFF FOR TONIGHT.

24:18.208 --> 24:20.208
GAME OVER.

24:21.959 --> 24:25.041
I KNOW IT'S A LITTLE CLOSE,
BUT CATHLEEN SAID HERSELF,

24:25.083 --> 24:27.041
SHE DOESN'T SETTLE.

24:27.083 --> 24:30.166
SHE HAS HER IDEA
OF WHAT SHE WANTS.
AND I'M THE NEXT BEST THING
TO BEING THERE.

24:30.208 --> 24:33.041
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE OKAY
WITH THIS, MARK?

24:33.083 --> 24:35.041
I MEAN, YOU'D BE MAKING
A CHILD.

24:35.083 --> 24:37.041
WHOA.
I'M NOT HAVING THE BABY.

24:37.083 --> 24:39.041
I'M JUST GONNA BE DOING
THE UNCLE THING.

24:39.083 --> 24:42.041
IT--IT SOUNDS SIMPLE NOW,
BUT SOMETIMES

24:42.083 --> 24:44.041
DONATIONS FROM
FAMILY MEMBERS CAN...
IT GETS--

24:44.083 --> 24:46.041
BE--
IT GETS COMPLICATED.

24:46.083 --> 24:47.917
YEAH.
WELL, MARK'S NOT COMPLICATED.

24:47.959 --> 24:49.667
I'M NOT COMPLICATED.

24:49.709 --> 24:53.709
I MEAN, HE WON'T
THINK TWICE ABOUT THIS.
YOU WON'T?

24:53.750 --> 24:56.750
NOPE. I PROBABLY HAVE
A FEW KIDS OUT THERE

24:56.792 --> 24:58.750
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT ALREADY.

24:58.792 --> 25:00.583
(laughs) IT'S A JOKE.
(laughter)

25:00.625 --> 25:02.125
IT'S PROBABLY A JOKE.

25:02.166 --> 25:03.583
THIS--THIS IS GOOD,
RIGHT?

25:03.625 --> 25:05.583
I MEAN,
MAYBE NOT US EXACTLY,

25:05.625 --> 25:08.542
BUT, UH, YOU KNOW,

25:08.583 --> 25:10.375
I'LL BE IN THE MIX.

25:10.417 --> 25:11.834
YES. IT'S JUST A LITTLE--

25:11.875 --> 25:14.500
I-I KNOW, AND--AND WE DON'T
HAVE TO AT ALL.

25:14.542 --> 25:16.834
IT'S JUST...

25:16.875 --> 25:18.834
NO. I WANT TO.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

25:18.875 --> 25:22.000
YOU'LL BE IN THE MIX,
AND THAT'S WHAT MATTERS.

25:25.083 --> 25:27.417
HAVE YOU SEEN, UH,
DR. MONTGOMERY?

25:27.458 --> 25:29.417
NOT LATELY.
DID YOU ASK AT RECEPTION?

25:29.458 --> 25:31.417
(sighs) YEAH.

25:31.458 --> 25:32.417
HEY.

25:32.458 --> 25:34.000
YOU'RE BACK.

25:34.041 --> 25:35.792
YEAH.

25:35.834 --> 25:38.875
AND YOU MET, UH, PETE.
MY FRIEND.

25:38.917 --> 25:41.375
KEVIN NELSON. HI.

25:41.417 --> 25:44.041
I CAME TO PICK UP
MY MEDICAL REPORT...

25:44.083 --> 25:45.667
FOR WORK.
UH-HUH.

25:45.709 --> 25:48.041
YOU KNOW, THEY CAN JUST
E-MAIL THAT TO YOU.

25:48.083 --> 25:50.792
(clears throat)

25:50.834 --> 25:52.834
(laughs)

25:52.875 --> 25:56.625
THEY CAN KIND OF...
E-MAIL YOU.

25:56.667 --> 26:00.041
OKAY. UH, I THOUGHT
I MIGHT SEE YOU AND...

26:00.083 --> 26:03.041
(police radio chatter)

26:03.083 --> 26:05.250
UH...

26:05.291 --> 26:07.291
MM.

26:07.333 --> 26:08.792
I'VE GOTTA TAKE THIS.

26:08.834 --> 26:10.875
OKAY. IT WAS NICE
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

26:10.917 --> 26:13.959
2-1-3 RESPONDING.

26:19.083 --> 26:20.834
PLEASE.

26:20.875 --> 26:23.041
LOOK, I WON'T BE
A DISTURBANCE.

26:23.083 --> 26:26.917
AND IF YOU CAN, UH,
JUST TALK INTO THE MIKE.

26:26.959 --> 26:28.208
(chuckles)

26:28.250 --> 26:30.583
YEAH, NO. SORRY, DUDE.

26:30.625 --> 26:32.625
WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO TELL JACK?

26:32.667 --> 26:34.041
HE'LL FIRE ME.

26:34.083 --> 26:36.959
LOOK, AND AFTER ALL THOSE
PRENATAL CLASSES WITH HIS WIFE

26:37.000 --> 26:39.709
AND DECORATING THE NURSERY,
I JUST--
HEY, HOW ABOUT
I TELL HIM SOMETHING?

26:39.750 --> 26:42.875
NO, DON'T.
YOUR WIFE IS ABOUT TO HAVE
A BABY, JACK.

26:42.917 --> 26:44.500
SO PUT DOWN THE BlackBerry,

26:44.542 --> 26:46.750
STOP SENDING ADAM
TO DO YOUR DIRTY WORK

26:46.792 --> 26:49.041
AND GET OVER HERE.

26:49.083 --> 26:51.750
GOT THAT, JACKASS?

26:54.166 --> 26:56.875
OKAY, USING A SPECULUM,

26:56.917 --> 26:59.041
I'M GOING TO INSERT
A CATHETER

26:59.083 --> 27:00.792
INTO YOUR UTERUS,

27:00.834 --> 27:02.834
WHERE THE SPERM
WILL BE RELEASED.

27:02.875 --> 27:04.542
MARK'S STUFF--

27:04.583 --> 27:07.250
IT WAS REALLY OKAY?
OH, YEAH, IT WAS EXCELLENT.

27:07.291 --> 27:09.041
MILLIONS AND MILLIONS
OF LITTLE GUYS.

27:09.083 --> 27:13.875
SO WITH ANY LUCK, THE "STUFF"
WILL SWIM RIGHT TO YOUR EGG,

27:13.917 --> 27:16.917
AND PRESTO--
YOU SHOULD HAVE AN EMBRYO.

27:16.959 --> 27:17.667
YAY.

27:17.709 --> 27:19.166
ALL RIGHT.

27:19.208 --> 27:22.667
AND HERE WE GO.

27:22.709 --> 27:23.792
NO!
NO!

27:23.834 --> 27:27.667
I CAN'T.
I CAN'T HAVE MARK INSIDE ME,

27:27.709 --> 27:29.667
THIS BROTHER SPERM TRAVELING
TO MY UTERUS.

27:29.709 --> 27:31.041
I KNOW, I KNOW.

27:31.083 --> 27:33.875
HONESTLY,
I LOVE YOUR BROTHER, BUT--
HE'S KIND OF A JERK.

27:33.917 --> 27:37.333
HE'S KIND OF A JERK.
WHY WOULD YOU EVEN SUGGEST THIS?

27:37.375 --> 27:39.375
I'M TRYING HERE, OKAY?
I JUST--
(Addison) LISTEN,
BOTH OF YOU,

27:39.417 --> 27:41.750
THIS ISN'T RIGHT FOR YOU,
AND THAT'S OKAY.

27:41.792 --> 27:43.959
I DON'T WANT ANYBODY'S BABY
BUT YOURS.

27:44.000 --> 27:45.625
I'M SORRY.

27:45.667 --> 27:47.959
SO WHAT DO WE DO?

27:48.000 --> 27:50.041
JUST GIVE UP,
NOT HAVE A KID?

27:50.083 --> 27:53.041
I JUST CAN'T DO THIS.
I CAN'T.

27:53.083 --> 27:55.041
THERE'S GOTTA BE
ANOTHER WAY.

27:55.083 --> 27:56.750
PLEASE.

27:56.792 --> 27:58.083
PLEASE...

27:58.125 --> 28:00.041
HELP US MAKE OUR BABY.

28:06.959 --> 28:08.208
I ACTUALLY THOUGHT THAT
THE BROTHER WAS OUR SOLUTION.

28:08.250 --> 28:10.208
NO, THEY WERE RIGHT.
HE'S A JERK.

28:10.250 --> 28:13.250
I WAS MOMENTARILY ATTRACTED
TO HIM, SO HE MUST BE.
(laughs)

28:13.291 --> 28:16.041
THE SWEET BROTHER
CAN'T MAKE BABIES.

28:16.083 --> 28:18.041
WHAT DOES THAT SAY
ABOUT NATURAL SELECTION?

28:18.083 --> 28:20.041
(sighs) WHAT WERE
HIS LEVELS AGAIN?

28:20.083 --> 28:22.667
UH, F.S.H. AND PROLACTIN
WERE WITHIN NORMAL LIMITS.

28:22.709 --> 28:24.625
HOW ABOUT TESTOSTERONE?

28:24.667 --> 28:26.041
BORDERLINE.
BORDERLINE LOW.

28:26.083 --> 28:28.041
YEAH, BUT NOT NONEXISTENT,

28:28.083 --> 28:30.041
WHICH MEANS
THERE MIGHT BE A WAY,

28:30.083 --> 28:33.875
AND IF THERE IS,
WE SHOULD FIND IT.

28:33.917 --> 28:35.792
SCREW NATURAL SELECTION.

28:35.834 --> 28:39.542
GENTLEMEN, PREPARE TO HAVE
YOUR LIVES TRANSFORMED.

28:39.583 --> 28:42.250
I PRESENT TO YOU...
DIAPER B. GONE.

28:42.291 --> 28:44.041
(man) WOW.
(men murmuring)

28:44.083 --> 28:45.709
I'M JACK GROSSMAN.

28:45.750 --> 28:48.000
WHICH ONE OF YOU JERKS
CALLED ME A JACKASS?

28:48.041 --> 28:49.875
THAT'D BE ME.

28:49.917 --> 28:52.458
UM, YOUR NAME'S JACK AND...

28:52.500 --> 28:54.917
YOU WERE ACTING
LIKE AN ASS.

28:54.959 --> 28:57.458
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT ME

28:57.500 --> 29:01.750
MY WIFE, MY WORK,

29:01.792 --> 29:04.417
MY LIFE, NOTHING.

29:04.458 --> 29:07.417
MR. GROSSMAN, HE WAS JUST
TRYING TO HELP. HE--
I KNOW THAT
YOU PAWNED OFF A CLASS

29:07.458 --> 29:10.000
THAT COULD HELP SAVE
YOUR BABY'S LIFE

29:10.041 --> 29:12.458
ON A GUY THAT MAKES YOU
LUNCH RESERVATIONS.
OH, YOU THINK
YOU'RE CLEVER, HUH?

29:12.500 --> 29:14.458
I KNOW.
YOU'RE A TOUGH GUY, OKAY?

29:14.500 --> 29:16.792
BUT THE TOUGH-GUY ACT IS NOT
GONNA WORK WITH BEING A FATHER.

29:16.834 --> 29:19.041
IT'S JUST NOT.
I'M DOING THIS MY WAY.

29:19.083 --> 29:22.458
MY WIFE IS GONNA STAY HOME
WITH OUR KID, AND I'M--
OKAY, BUT YOUR WIFE
IS NOT THERE TO DO YOUR JOB.

29:22.500 --> 29:25.333
YOU CAN'T CHECK OUT, JACK.
YOU GOTTA SHOW UP.

29:25.375 --> 29:27.333
IN FACT, YOU HAVE GOTTA
SCREW THINGS UP

29:27.375 --> 29:30.041
BEFORE YOU EVEN HAVE
THE FIRST CLUE AB--

29:30.083 --> 29:31.959
HOW MANY OF YOU GUYS
HAVE FIGURED OUT

29:32.000 --> 29:35.041
WHAT IT MEANS TO BE A FATHER?
(man) NOT ME.

29:35.083 --> 29:38.250
WELL, I-I DON'T KNOW MUCH,
BUT I KNOW MORE THAN THIS GUY.

29:38.291 --> 29:39.875
(men murmur)

29:39.917 --> 29:41.083
THIS KID IS COMING,

29:41.125 --> 29:44.458
WHETHER YOU'RE READY FOR IT
OR NOT.

29:44.500 --> 29:46.709
YOU THINK I DON'T KNOW THAT?

29:46.750 --> 29:50.041
YOU THINK IT DOESN'T
KEEP ME UP AT NIGHT?

29:50.083 --> 29:53.041
ALL I WANT FOR THAT KID
IS TO BE SAFE AND TO BE HAPPY,

29:53.083 --> 29:55.667
AND I'M DOING EVERYTHING
THAT I KNOW HOW TO DO.

29:55.709 --> 29:58.041
I BELIEVE YOU.
NOW DO MORE.

29:58.083 --> 30:01.041
I MEAN, YOU CAME DOWN HERE
TO YELL AT A PEDIATRICIAN,

30:01.083 --> 30:03.041
SO DON'T TELL ME
YOU DON'T CARE ENOUGH.

30:03.083 --> 30:06.000
(men murmuring)

30:09.000 --> 30:11.875
I GOT THIS.

30:11.917 --> 30:14.000
AM I, UH...

30:14.041 --> 30:16.041
I'M NOT FIRED?

30:16.083 --> 30:18.291
NO.

30:18.333 --> 30:22.375
BUT THERE'S NO WAY
YOU'RE WATCHING ME DO THIS.

30:22.417 --> 30:24.041
WELL, COME ON.

30:24.083 --> 30:27.041
LET'S SHOW THIS GUY
HOW TO ROCK THIS, RIGHT?
(man) YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

30:27.083 --> 30:29.250
COME ON.
OKAY, YES.
SHOW HIM HOW IT'S DONE.

30:32.583 --> 30:35.083
SO DID OFFICER MANLY
MAKE A MOVE?

30:35.125 --> 30:36.959
(sighs)

30:37.000 --> 30:39.834
YOU REALLY WANT
TO HEAR ABOUT THIS?

30:39.875 --> 30:43.291
THIS IS WHAT FRIENDS DO.
RIGHT?

30:43.333 --> 30:45.125
NO SEX TALK.
THAT'S OFF-LIMITS.

30:45.166 --> 30:47.208
UH, I DON'T USUALLY
TALK ABOUT IT.

30:47.250 --> 30:48.917
I'M MORE OF A DO-IT GUY.

30:48.959 --> 30:51.041
OH, YEAH. GOOD TO KNOW.

30:51.083 --> 30:55.166
AND THE OFFICER DID NOT GET
A CHANCE TO MOVE.

30:55.208 --> 30:56.959
MY MAN CHOICES LATELY--

30:57.041 --> 30:58.208
HAVE BEEN ME?

30:58.250 --> 31:01.041
AND TRUNK.

31:01.083 --> 31:02.166
(chuckles)

31:02.208 --> 31:04.583
SAY YES.

31:04.625 --> 31:06.041
IT'S THAT SIMPLE?

31:06.083 --> 31:09.041
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT
THERE HAVE BEEN MISFIRES.

31:09.083 --> 31:10.333
DATING IS A NUMBERS GAME.

31:10.375 --> 31:12.959
YOU GET OUT THERE AS MUCH
AS YOU CAN AND SEE WHAT WORKS.

31:13.000 --> 31:14.667
VOLUME DATING,
THAT'S YOUR PHILOSOPHY?

31:14.709 --> 31:16.667
MY POINT IS,
MOST OF THE TIME,

31:16.709 --> 31:18.667
YOU'RE NOT GONNA FIND
A RIGHT FIT.

31:18.709 --> 31:21.041
AND SOMETIMES,
IT'S THE LAST PERSON YOU'D THINK

31:21.083 --> 31:23.458
WHO MAKES YOU HAPPY.

31:23.500 --> 31:26.083
AND... YEAH, I'M OUT THERE.

31:28.083 --> 31:29.208
GOOD.

31:29.250 --> 31:30.959
GOOD ADVICE...

31:31.000 --> 31:32.875
FOR US.

31:32.917 --> 31:35.041
I GOTTA GO...

31:35.083 --> 31:37.000
TAKE CARE OF
CATHLEEN AND GEOFFREY.

31:40.125 --> 31:42.083
SO WE THINK
WE FOUND SOMETHING.

31:42.125 --> 31:45.041
IT'S A NEW PROCEDURE CALLED
TESTICULAR SPERM EXTRACTION.

31:45.083 --> 31:47.709
OKAY, WHAT'S THAT?
SPERM SEARCH AND RESCUE.

31:47.750 --> 31:49.041
WE GO INSIDE THE TESTICLE

31:49.083 --> 31:51.041
TO LOOK FOR
A FEW VIABLE SPERM,

31:51.083 --> 31:53.166
WHICH WE THEN IMPLANT
INTO CATHLEEN'S EGGS

31:53.208 --> 31:56.166
TO MAKE A CHILD.
YOU CAN DO THAT?

31:56.208 --> 31:58.166
YES. WE USE
A SURGICAL MICROSCOPE

31:58.208 --> 31:59.917
TO ISOLATE
SPERM-PRODUCING TISSUE.

31:59.959 --> 32:02.583
IF WE FIND EVEN ONE SPERM,
YOU HAVE A SHOT.

32:02.625 --> 32:04.583
WOW.
THIS IS SO FRIGGIN' COOL.

32:04.625 --> 32:06.667
IT'S LIKE RAMBO TIME.

32:06.709 --> 32:09.208
I-INSIDE MY TESTICLES?

32:09.250 --> 32:11.667
YES.
YEAH.

32:16.333 --> 32:19.041
I KNOW WHY, WHY YOU'VE
BEEN AVOIDING ME. IT--

32:19.083 --> 32:21.041
WHAT? WHAT?

32:21.083 --> 32:23.083
I...

32:23.125 --> 32:26.125
OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.

32:26.166 --> 32:28.750
YOU DO?
YES!

32:28.792 --> 32:31.750
I WAS STUPID TO THINK
WE COULD HAVE UNEMOTIONAL SEX,

32:31.792 --> 32:33.959
OR ATTEMPTED SEX.

32:34.000 --> 32:37.041
WE--WE CARE ABOUT EACH OTHER.
WE'RE FRIENDS.

32:37.083 --> 32:39.750
FRIENDS WITH BENEFITS
NEVER WORKS.

32:39.792 --> 32:41.291
I WAS WRONG.

32:41.333 --> 32:44.041
THANK YOU.

32:44.083 --> 32:47.041
SO IT WAS THE SEX? THAT'S WHY
YOU'VE BEEN AVOIDING ME?

32:47.083 --> 32:49.291
IT WAS THE SEX.
GOOD.

32:49.333 --> 32:51.083
(sighs)
SO WE'RE GOOD?

32:51.125 --> 32:53.333
WE'RE GOOD.

32:53.375 --> 32:54.709
GOOD.

32:56.083 --> 32:58.375
OKAY, GEOFFREY,

32:58.417 --> 33:00.417
ONCE I GET INSIDE,

33:00.458 --> 33:02.333
YOU MIGHT FEEL
A SLIGHT PULLING,

33:02.375 --> 33:04.041
SOME DISCOMFORT.

33:04.083 --> 33:06.333
IF IT GETS TOO BAD,
WE CAN STOP.

33:06.375 --> 33:09.041
AND THEN IF DR. MONTGOMERY
LOCATES ANY SPERM,

33:09.083 --> 33:11.750
I'LL EXTRACT CATHLEEN'S EGGS.

33:11.792 --> 33:13.917
YOU CAN DO THIS, HONEY.

33:13.959 --> 33:15.959
I LOVE YOU, BABE.

33:16.000 --> 33:18.041
OKAY, ON THREE.

33:18.083 --> 33:20.333
ONE...

33:20.375 --> 33:22.917
TWO...

33:22.959 --> 33:24.000
THREE.

33:28.625 --> 33:30.583
OKAY...

33:30.625 --> 33:32.375
I'M GOING INSIDE,

33:32.417 --> 33:34.959
TAKING A LOOK AROUND,

33:35.000 --> 33:38.834
TRYING TO FIND THAT...

33:38.875 --> 33:41.125
ONE SWIMMER.

33:41.166 --> 33:43.125
WHAT IF
SHE DOESN'T FIND ANYTHING?

33:43.166 --> 33:46.000
WHAT IF
THERE'S NOTHING THERE?

33:46.041 --> 33:48.166
I LOVE YOU NO MATTER WHAT.

33:52.083 --> 33:54.792
WHAT'S GOING ON?

33:54.834 --> 33:56.208
THE HOSPITAL JUST CALLED.

33:56.250 --> 34:00.250
I'VE--I'VE GOTTA GO GET,
UH, WENDELL.

34:00.291 --> 34:02.250
NATE'S NOT GOING TO MAKE IT.

34:12.041 --> 34:14.166
ANYTHING?

34:14.208 --> 34:17.500
NO, NOT...

34:20.083 --> 34:23.041
WAIT. WHAT'S THAT?

34:23.083 --> 34:25.083
I HAVE ONE?
YOU FOUND IT?

34:25.125 --> 34:28.083
MAYBE.
I JUST NEED TO GRAB THIS.

34:28.125 --> 34:30.875
COME ON, YOU BASTARD.

34:30.917 --> 34:33.208
SORRY.

34:33.250 --> 34:36.208
♪♪♪

34:39.083 --> 34:41.041
GOT IT.

34:41.083 --> 34:44.000
YOU--YOU DID?
HOLD ON A MINUTE.
WE'RE CHECKING.

34:44.041 --> 34:46.417
♪♪♪

34:46.458 --> 34:49.041
YEAH. THERE YOU GO.

34:49.083 --> 34:52.041
THAT'S MY KID.
THAT'S YOUR KID.

34:52.083 --> 34:55.000
♪♪♪

34:58.083 --> 35:01.041
NATE WAS RIGHT ABOUT HIS HEART.
IT WAS SHOT.

35:01.083 --> 35:03.041
IT WASN'T ME?

35:03.083 --> 35:06.750
NO, NO. HE WAS LIVING
ON BORROWED TIME.

35:06.792 --> 35:09.041
♪♪♪

35:09.083 --> 35:10.917
I'M SORRY.

35:10.959 --> 35:12.917
I KNOW HE WAS YOUR FRIEND.

35:12.959 --> 35:15.333
NATE LOST HIS WIFE, TOO.

35:15.375 --> 35:19.041
AND THEN...
HE WAS AT THE HOME.

35:19.083 --> 35:23.041
YOU WANT TO KNOW WHY
WE FIGHT? I'LL TELL YOU WHY.

35:23.083 --> 35:25.041
ON THOSE DAYS,
YOU WAKE UP THINKING,

35:25.083 --> 35:31.291
TODAY SOMETHING HAPPENS
BESIDES THIS... DEATH MARCH.

35:31.333 --> 35:33.041
OUR LIVES...

35:33.083 --> 35:35.291
THEY CHANGE.

35:35.333 --> 35:37.291
FAIR ENOUGH, WE'RE OLD.

35:37.333 --> 35:41.250
BUT THEY DON'T
HAVE TO BE OVER.

35:41.291 --> 35:43.875
♪♪♪

35:43.917 --> 35:47.000
DAMN... IT FELT GOOD.

35:47.041 --> 35:48.125
TO FIGHT?

35:48.166 --> 35:50.125
♪♪♪

35:50.166 --> 35:52.166
I HATE BINGO.

35:52.208 --> 35:53.667
(chuckles)
(laughs)

35:53.709 --> 35:56.041
SO DID NATE.

35:56.083 --> 35:57.333
YOUR GRANDMA...

35:57.375 --> 36:00.041
SHE WAS WHAT I LIVED FOR.

36:00.083 --> 36:02.709
♪♪♪

36:02.750 --> 36:05.041
YOU'LL SEE,
WHEN YOU'RE LIKE ME,

36:05.083 --> 36:08.542
YOU'LL WISH YOU'D FOUGHT MORE
YOUR WHOLE LIFE.

36:08.583 --> 36:13.125
YOU'LL MISS CARING THAT MUCH
ABOUT ANYTHING.

36:13.166 --> 36:16.542
♪♪♪

36:21.250 --> 36:24.250
♪♪♪

